119.6	Polymer	Polymer	A polymer is a large molecule composed of repeating structural units. These sub-units are typically connected by covalent chemical bonds. Although the term polymer is sometimes taken to refer to plastics, it actually encompasses a large class of compounds comprising both natural and synthetic materials with a wide variety of properties.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Single_Polymer_Chains_AFM.jpg/175px-Single_Polymer_Chains_AFM.jpg
